From: eventcv-feedstock
Subject: Relax numpy upper bound to allow numpy 2.x

numpy is a pure runtime dependency here (rust-numpy 0.29 resolves it through
the Python API at runtime, with no build-time C-ABI linkage), so the <2 cap is
unnecessary. It also makes the package unbuildable on Python 3.13, for which no
numpy<2 exists. Allow the full 1.24 -> 2.x range.

--- a/pyproject.toml
+++ b/pyproject.toml
@@ -14,7 +14,7 @@
 license = { file = "LICENSE" }
 authors = [
   { name = "Adam Hines", email = "a.david.hines@gmail.com"}
 ]
 dependencies = [
-    "numpy>=1.24,<2"
+    "numpy>=1.24"
 ]
